BERRY E. CLARK v. STATE OF MARYLAND. [No. 109,

October Term, 1933.]

Decided January 30th, 1934.

The cause was argued before Bond, C. J., Adkins, Offutt, and Sloan, JJ.

F. Bernard Welsh, with whom were Albert M. Bouic, E. Barrett Prettyman, and Thomas L. Dawson, on the brief, for the appellant. Wm. Preston Lane, Jr., Attorney General; G. O. Anderson, Assistant Attorney General, and Stedman Prescott, State’s Attorney for Montgomery County, submitting on brief, for the State.

The opinion was delivered

per Curiam.
